==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪbɪt|-ɪbɪt]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

#{{transitive}} To [[display]] or [[show]] (something) for others to see, especially at an [[exhibition]] or [[contest]]
#: ''He wanted to '''exhibit''' his baseball cards.''
#{{transitive}} To [[demonstrate]]
#: ''The players '''exhibited''' great skill.''
#{{transitive}} To [[submit]] ([[evidence]]) to a [[court]]
#: ''I now '''exhibit''' this bloody hammer.''
#{{intransitive}} To display publicly
#: ''Will you be '''exhibiting''' this year?''

====Synonyms====
*(''transitive: display or show (something) for others to see''): [[display]], [[show]], [[show off]]
*(''demonstrate''): [[demonstrate]], [[show]]
*(''submit to a court''):
*(''intransitive: display publicly''):

